locality: San Pedro Riparian National Conservation Area, on low eroded bluffs west of the San Pedro River, 0.4 air miles NW of Boquillas (ruins) and 1.2 air miles SW of Contention (ruins) about 4.1 air miles NNW of Presidio Santa Cruz de Terrenate, associated with Larrea and other desert shrubs.

North of East Marsh Station (or Pantano) Road north of Cienega Creek, 6.3 miles east-northeast of the Mountain View Exit (Exit 281) along Interstate Highway 10, 1.4 air mile northwest of Cross Hill and 6.85 air miles east-southeast of Vail.
